{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-81466fe281b9ee2f", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\"arxiv_id\": \"2512.20151\", \"title\": \"QuarkAudio Technical Report\", \"authors\": [\"Chengwei Liu\", \"Haoyin Yan\", \"Shaofei Xue\", \"Xiaotao Liang\", \"Xiaofu Chen\", \"Bin Gong\", \"Zheng Xue\", \"Gang Song\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"eess.AS\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"codec_vae\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u7f16\\u8f91\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u7edf\\u4e00\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u91cf\\u5316-RVQ\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u8bed\\u4e49\\u58f0\\u5b66-\\u8bed\\u4e49\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u8bed\\u4e49\\u58f0\\u5b66-\\u58f0\\u5b66\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present H-Codec, a unified discrete audio tokenizer that integrates self-supervised learning representations into the tokenization process via dual-stream (acoustic and semantic) quantization, achieving remarkable audio reconstruction quality at a low frame rate.\", \"We introduce advanced H-Codec variants, including H-Codec-1.5 with a dynamic frame-rate mechanism for adaptive temporal resolution and H-Codec-2.0 extending the sampling rate to 48 kHz for higher fidelity.\", \"We propose QuarkAudio, a unified decoder-only autoregressive language model framework that uses task-specific conditional information and special task tokens to distinguish and unify multiple audio processing and generation tasks within a single set of shared weights.\", \"We extend unified audio generation to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions, covering both speech semantic editing and audio event editing.\", \"We demonstrate that QuarkAudio achieves competitive or comparable high-fidelity generation performance against state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across speech restoration, target speaker extraction, speech separation, voice conversion, and language-queried audio source separation tasks.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2408.01032\", \"title\": \"WavTokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Compared as a codec baseline in speech and multi-domain audio reconstruction.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2501.01444\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Used for codec speech reconstruction evaluation (test-clean) and as training data for generation tasks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavLM\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained SSL model used by H-Codec-1.5 to extract semantic features\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HuBERT\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained SSL model used by H-Codec-2.0 to extract semantic features and by QuarkAudio LM for audio condition features\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Encodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"H-Codec acoustic encoder inherits similar convolution structure from Encodec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vocos\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"H-Codec decoder uses Vocos-style ISTFT head for waveform reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"T5-base\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to extract text caption embeddings for QuarkAudio LM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Decoder backbone architecture used for QuarkAudio LM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DAC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"X-Codec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"X-Codec2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BiCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UniCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FlexiCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiMO-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"XY-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BigCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Baichuan-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Mimi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GLM4-Voice-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaSE-G1\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for SE, PLC, and SS tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LauraTSE\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Metis-VC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FlowSep\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Language-guided Audio Source Separation (LASS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceCraft\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceCraft-X\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxBox\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Large-scale speech training data for H-Codec and downstream tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FMA-full\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Music training data for H-Codec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MUSDB18-HQ\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Music training data for H-Codec and evaluation data for music reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioSet\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"General audio training data for H-Codec and evaluation data for general audio reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"General audio training data for H-Codec and LASS/EDIT-A tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech test-clean\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for speech reconstruction at 16 kHz\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Seed-TTS-Eval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for speech reconstruction at 24 kHz\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Noise corpus used for simulating mixture training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FSD50K\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Noise corpus used for simulating mixture training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2020 DNS Challenge test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2022 PLC Challenge blind test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Packet Loss Concealment (PLC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Libri2Mix clean test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Libri2Mix noisy test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Source Separation (SS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VCTK dataset\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2024 DCASE LASS validation set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Language-guided Audio Source Separation (LASS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SEED-ZH\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S) with 100 utterances\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SEED-EN\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S) with 100 utterances\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAP_FreeSound\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Data source for building Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A) training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAP_FreeSound 100 samples\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioSet eval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for general audio reconstruction at 48 kHz and Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"PESQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for perceptual speech quality evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"STOI\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for short-time objective intelligibility evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UTMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for naturalness evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SPK-SIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speaker similarity evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WER\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for word error rate evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Mel loss\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for mel-spectrogram reconstruction loss evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"STFT loss\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for STFT reconstruction loss evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNSMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speech enhancement evaluation (SIG/BAK/OVRL)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"NISQA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speech quality evaluation in VC task\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speaker similarity evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"PLCMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for packet loss concealment evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FAD\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for audio generation quality evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAPScore\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for text-audio alignment evaluation in LASS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAPScore_A\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for text-audio alignment evaluation in LASS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MSD\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for multi-scale spectral distortion evaluation in audio event editing\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Many existing audio processing and generation models rely on task-specific architectures, resulting in fragmented development efforts and limited extensibility. It is therefore promising to design a unified framework capable of handling multiple tasks, while providing robust instruction and audio understanding and high-quality audio generation. This requires a compatible paradigm design, a powerful backbone, and a high-fidelity audio reconstruction module. To meet these requirements, this technical report introduces QuarkAudio, a decoder-only autoregressive (AR) LM-based generative framework that unifies multiple tasks. The framework includes a unified discrete audio tokenizer, H-Codec, which incorporates self-supervised learning (SSL) representations into the tokenization and reconstruction process. We further propose several improvements to H-Codec, such as a dynamic frame-rate mechanism and extending the audio sampling rate to 48 kHz. QuarkAudio unifies tasks by using task-specific conditional information as the conditioning sequence of the decoder-only LM, and predicting discrete target audio tokens in an AR manner. The framework supports a wide range of audio processing and generation tasks, including speech restoration (SR), target speaker extraction (TSE), speech separation (SS), voice conversion (VC), and language-queried audio source separation (LASS). In addition, we extend downstream tasks to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions (including speech semantic editing and audio event editing). Experimental results show that H-Codec achieves high-quality audio reconstruction with a low frame rate, improving both the efficiency and performance of downstream audio generation, and that QuarkAudio delivers competitive or comparable performance to state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across multiple tasks.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T06:47:25.230239\"}\n===2603.28086===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2603.28086\", \"title\": \"MOSS-VoiceGenerator: Create Realistic Voices with Natural Language Descriptions\", \"authors\": [\"Kexin Huang\", \"Liwei Fan\", \"Botian Jiang\", \"Yaozhou Jiang\", \"Qian Tu\", \"Jie Zhu\", \"Yuqian Zhang\", \"Yiwei Zhao\", \"Chenchen Yang\", \"Zhaoye Fei\", \"Shimin Li\", \"Xiaogui Yang\", \"Qinyuan Cheng\", \"Xipeng Qiu\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-NL\\u63cf\\u8ff0\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present MOSS-VoiceGenerator, a fully open-source instruction-driven TTS model that generates realistic and expressive speech directly from natural language descriptions, without requiring any reference audio.\", \"We construct a data pipeline suitable for instruction-based tasks, along with a richly annotated dataset sourced from cinematic content, where our developed embedding and annotation models enable cost-effective data augmentation.\", \"Extensive evaluations show that MOSS-VoiceGenerator performs exceptionally well in subjective evaluations and achieves competitive performance in objective evaluations.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2303.15343\", \"title\": \"Whisper-large-v3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to filter out non-Chinese and non-English audio\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Architecture design adopted for the model, utilizing delay pattern and audio tokenization.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Audio tokenizer used for encoding/decoding audio waveforms, using the first 16 RVQ layers.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DiariZen\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Speaker diarization model used to identify and segment different speakers in Phase 1 data collection.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MossFormer2_SE_48K\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Denoising model used to extract clean speech from noisy acoustic conditions in Phase 1.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNSMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Quality filtering metric used with a threshold of >= 3.0 to retain audio samples post-denoising.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-Transcribe-Diarize\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate accurate per-speaker transcriptions for single-speaker filtering.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used for transcribing audio, selected for its superior performance in numbers, symbols, and punctuation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-2.5 Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate detailed descriptions for about 5000 hours of audio in Phase 1.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-32B-A3B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to convert detailed audio descriptions into natural language timbre instructions.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Thinking\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Fine-tuned on Phase 1 data to create a dedicated speech description model for large-scale automatic annotation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate diverse text timbre instructions as queries for style-guided audio mining.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Backbone model providing checkpoint weights for training the 1.7B and 8B models.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"InstructTTSEval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Public benchmark used for objective evaluation, containing 6000 test cases across 3 tasks and 2 languages.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-TTS-Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline supporting only fixed voice editing.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o-mini-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline supporting only fixed voice editing.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxInstruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline requiring reference audio.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceSculptor-VD\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MIMO-Audio-7B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective and subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-TTS-VD\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective and subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiniMax Voice Design\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Voice design from natural language aims to generate speaker timbres directly from free-form textual descriptions, allowing users to create voices tailored to specific roles, personalities, and emotions. Such controllable voice creation benefits a wide range of downstream applications-including storytelling, game dubbing, role-play agents, and conversational assistants, making it a significant task for modern Text-to-Speech models. However, existing models are largely trained on carefully recorded studio data, which produces speech that is clean and well-articulated, yet lacks the lived-in qualities of real human voices. To address these limitations, we present MOSS-VoiceGenerator, an open-source instruction-driven voice generation model that creates new timbres directly from natural language prompts. Motivated by the hypothesis that exposure to real-world acoustic variation produces more perceptually natural voices, we train on large-scale expressive speech data sourced from cinematic content. Subjective preference studies demonstrate its superiority in overall performance, instruction-following, and naturalness compared to other voice design models.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T05:21:22.651227\"}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "2455c186-f17a-44bc-acbe-671a967e7aee", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T05:53:26.129Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\"arxiv_id\": \"2512.20151\", \"title\": \"QuarkAudio Technical Report\", \"authors\": [\"Chengwei Liu\", \"Haoyin Yan\", \"Shaofei Xue\", \"Xiaotao Liang\", \"Xiaofu Chen\", \"Bin Gong\", \"Zheng Xue\", \"Gang Song\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"eess.AS\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"codec_vae\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u7f16\\u8f91\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u7edf\\u4e00\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u91cf\\u5316-RVQ\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u8bed\\u4e49\\u58f0\\u5b66-\\u8bed\\u4e49\", \"\\u538b\\u7f29/\\u8bed\\u4e49\\u58f0\\u5b66-\\u58f0\\u5b66\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present H-Codec, a unified discrete audio tokenizer that integrates self-supervised learning representations into the tokenization process via dual-stream (acoustic and semantic) quantization, achieving remarkable audio reconstruction quality at a low frame rate.\", \"We introduce advanced H-Codec variants, including H-Codec-1.5 with a dynamic frame-rate mechanism for adaptive temporal resolution and H-Codec-2.0 extending the sampling rate to 48 kHz for higher fidelity.\", \"We propose QuarkAudio, a unified decoder-only autoregressive language model framework that uses task-specific conditional information and special task tokens to distinguish and unify multiple audio processing and generation tasks within a single set of shared weights.\", \"We extend unified audio generation to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions, covering both speech semantic editing and audio event editing.\", \"We demonstrate that QuarkAudio achieves competitive or comparable high-fidelity generation performance against state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across speech restoration, target speaker extraction, speech separation, voice conversion, and language-queried audio source separation tasks.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2408.01032\", \"title\": \"WavTokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Compared as a codec baseline in speech and multi-domain audio reconstruction.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2501.01444\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Used for codec speech reconstruction evaluation (test-clean) and as training data for generation tasks.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavLM\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained SSL model used by H-Codec-1.5 to extract semantic features\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HuBERT\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained SSL model used by H-Codec-2.0 to extract semantic features and by QuarkAudio LM for audio condition features\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Encodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"H-Codec acoustic encoder inherits similar convolution structure from Encodec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vocos\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"H-Codec decoder uses Vocos-style ISTFT head for waveform reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"T5-base\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to extract text caption embeddings for QuarkAudio LM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaMA\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Decoder backbone architecture used for QuarkAudio LM\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DAC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"X-Codec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"X-Codec2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BiCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UniCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FlexiCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiMO-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"XY-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BigCodec\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Baichuan-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Mimi\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GLM4-Voice-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Codec baseline compared against in audio reconstruction experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LLaSE-G1\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for SE, PLC, and SS tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LauraTSE\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Metis-VC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FlowSep\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Language-guided Audio Source Separation (LASS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceCraft\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceCraft-X\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Downstream task baseline for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxBox\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Large-scale speech training data for H-Codec and downstream tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FMA-full\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Music training data for H-Codec\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MUSDB18-HQ\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Music training data for H-Codec and evaluation data for music reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioSet\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"General audio training data for H-Codec and evaluation data for general audio reconstruction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"General audio training data for H-Codec and LASS/EDIT-A tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech test-clean\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for speech reconstruction at 16 kHz\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Seed-TTS-Eval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for speech reconstruction at 24 kHz\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Noise corpus used for simulating mixture training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FSD50K\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Noise corpus used for simulating mixture training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2020 DNS Challenge test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2022 PLC Challenge blind test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Packet Loss Concealment (PLC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Libri2Mix clean test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Libri2Mix noisy test set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Source Separation (SS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VCTK dataset\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"2024 DCASE LASS validation set\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Language-guided Audio Source Separation (LASS)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SEED-ZH\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S) with 100 utterances\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SEED-EN\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Speech Semantic Editing (EDIT-S) with 100 utterances\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAP_FreeSound\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Data source for building Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A) training data\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAP_FreeSound 100 samples\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioSet eval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Evaluation dataset for general audio reconstruction at 48 kHz and Audio Event Editing (EDIT-A)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"PESQ\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for perceptual speech quality evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"STOI\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for short-time objective intelligibility evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UTMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for naturalness evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SPK-SIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speaker similarity evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WER\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for word error rate evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Mel loss\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for mel-spectrogram reconstruction loss evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"STFT loss\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for STFT reconstruction loss evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNSMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speech enhancement evaluation (SIG/BAK/OVRL)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"NISQA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speech quality evaluation in VC task\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SIM\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for speaker similarity evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"PLCMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for packet loss concealment evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"FAD\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for audio generation quality evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAPScore\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for text-audio alignment evaluation in LASS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAPScore_A\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for text-audio alignment evaluation in LASS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MSD\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Metric for multi-scale spectral distortion evaluation in audio event editing\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Many existing audio processing and generation models rely on task-specific architectures, resulting in fragmented development efforts and limited extensibility. It is therefore promising to design a unified framework capable of handling multiple tasks, while providing robust instruction and audio understanding and high-quality audio generation. This requires a compatible paradigm design, a powerful backbone, and a high-fidelity audio reconstruction module. To meet these requirements, this technical report introduces QuarkAudio, a decoder-only autoregressive (AR) LM-based generative framework that unifies multiple tasks. The framework includes a unified discrete audio tokenizer, H-Codec, which incorporates self-supervised learning (SSL) representations into the tokenization and reconstruction process. We further propose several improvements to H-Codec, such as a dynamic frame-rate mechanism and extending the audio sampling rate to 48 kHz. QuarkAudio unifies tasks by using task-specific conditional information as the conditioning sequence of the decoder-only LM, and predicting discrete target audio tokens in an AR manner. The framework supports a wide range of audio processing and generation tasks, including speech restoration (SR), target speaker extraction (TSE), speech separation (SS), voice conversion (VC), and language-queried audio source separation (LASS). In addition, we extend downstream tasks to universal free-form audio editing guided by natural language instructions (including speech semantic editing and audio event editing). Experimental results show that H-Codec achieves high-quality audio reconstruction with a low frame rate, improving both the efficiency and performance of downstream audio generation, and that QuarkAudio delivers competitive or comparable performance to state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across multiple tasks.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T06:47:25.230239\"}\n===2603.28086===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2603.28086\", \"title\": \"MOSS-VoiceGenerator: Create Realistic Voices with Natural Language Descriptions\", \"authors\": [\"Kexin Huang\", \"Liwei Fan\", \"Botian Jiang\", \"Yaozhou Jiang\", \"Qian Tu\", \"Jie Zhu\", \"Yuqian Zhang\", \"Yiwei Zhao\", \"Chenchen Yang\", \"Zhaoye Fei\", \"Shimin Li\", \"Xiaogui Yang\", \"Qinyuan Cheng\", \"Xipeng Qiu\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-AR-LLM\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-NL\\u63cf\\u8ff0\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\"], \"contributions\": [\"We present MOSS-VoiceGenerator, a fully open-source instruction-driven TTS model that generates realistic and expressive speech directly from natural language descriptions, without requiring any reference audio.\", \"We construct a data pipeline suitable for instruction-based tasks, along with a richly annotated dataset sourced from cinematic content, where our developed embedding and annotation models enable cost-effective data augmentation.\", \"Extensive evaluations show that MOSS-VoiceGenerator performs exceptionally well in subjective evaluations and achieves competitive performance in objective evaluations.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2303.15343\", \"title\": \"Whisper-large-v3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to filter out non-Chinese and non-English audio\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Architecture design adopted for the model, utilizing delay pattern and audio tokenization.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-Audio-Tokenizer\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Audio tokenizer used for encoding/decoding audio waveforms, using the first 16 RVQ layers.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DiariZen\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Speaker diarization model used to identify and segment different speakers in Phase 1 data collection.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MossFormer2_SE_48K\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Denoising model used to extract clean speech from noisy acoustic conditions in Phase 1.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNSMOS\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Quality filtering metric used with a threshold of >= 3.0 to retain audio samples post-denoising.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MOSS-Transcribe-Diarize\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate accurate per-speaker transcriptions for single-speaker filtering.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used for transcribing audio, selected for its superior performance in numbers, symbols, and punctuation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-2.5 Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate detailed descriptions for about 5000 hours of audio in Phase 1.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-32B-A3B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to convert detailed audio descriptions into natural language timbre instructions.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Thinking\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Fine-tuned on Phase 1 data to create a dedicated speech description model for large-scale automatic annotation.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-5\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate diverse text timbre instructions as queries for style-guided audio mining.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Backbone model providing checkpoint weights for training the 1.7B and 8B models.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"InstructTTSEval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Public benchmark used for objective evaluation, containing 6000 test cases across 3 tasks and 2 languages.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-TTS-Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline supporting only fixed voice editing.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o-mini-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline supporting only fixed voice editing.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxInstruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline requiring reference audio.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceSculptor-VD\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MIMO-Audio-7B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective and subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-TTS-VD\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Objective and subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiniMax Voice Design\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Subjective evaluation baseline model.\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Voice design from natural language aims to generate speaker timbres directly from free-form textual descriptions, allowing users to create voices tailored to specific roles, personalities, and emotions. Such controllable voice creation benefits a wide range of downstream applications-including storytelling, game dubbing, role-play agents, and conversational assistants, making it a significant task for modern Text-to-Speech models. However, existing models are largely trained on carefully recorded studio data, which produces speech that is clean and well-articulated, yet lacks the lived-in qualities of real human voices. To address these limitations, we present MOSS-VoiceGenerator, an open-source instruction-driven voice generation model that creates new timbres directly from natural language prompts. Motivated by the hypothesis that exposure to real-world acoustic variation produces more perceptually natural voices, we train on large-scale expressive speech data sourced from cinematic content. Subjective preference studies demonstrate its superiority in overall performance, instruction-following, and naturalness compared to other voice design models.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T05:21:22.651227\"}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-94d0cd00b69d5e1d", "type": "tool_result", "content": "[{\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2502.03128\", \"title\": \"Metis: A Foundation Speech Generation Model with Masked Generative Pre-training\", \"authors\": [\"Yuancheng Wang\", \"Jiachen Zheng\", \"Junan Zhang\", \"Xueyao Zhang\", \"Huan Liao\", \"Zhizheng Wu\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.LG\", \"eess.AS\", \"eess.SP\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u7edf\\u4e00\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-\\u53c2\\u8003\\u8bed\\u97f3\"], \"contributions\": [\"Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens using large-scale unlabeled speech data without any task-specific condition.\", \"Metis efficiently adapts to various speech generation tasks through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, achieving state-of-the-art results with limited data and trainable parameters.\", \"Metis supports multimodal conditional inputs during fine-tuning, enabling diverse speech generation tasks and novel applications like text-guided target speaker extraction through multi-task combinations.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2409.00750\", \"title\": \"MaskGCT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS experiments on SeedTTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"w2v-bert-2.0\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SSL Token extractor using its 17th layer features for the first stage discrete representation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DAC\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Acoustic codec architecture used for residual vector quantization to extract acoustic tokens\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vocos\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Decoder used in the acoustic token extraction stage to preserve acoustic details\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Emilia\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"100K hours subset used for pre-training and 1K/10K hours used for TTS fine-tuning\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriTTS\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"0.58K hours used for TTS fine-tuning\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LRW\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for Lip-to-Speech (L2S) task\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LRS2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for Lip-to-Speech (L2S) task\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LRS3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for Lip-to-Speech (L2S) task\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SeedTTS test-en\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for zero-shot TTS and VC evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SeedTTS test-zh\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for zero-shot TTS evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriSpeech test-clean\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for generalization validation of TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VCTK\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for Voice Conversion (VC) evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LibriMix\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE) evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"EmiliaMix\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for Target Speaker Extraction (TSE) evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DNS2020\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set (with/without reverb and real recordings) for Speech Enhancement (SE) evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SeedVC\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Test set for generalization validation of VC\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavLM TDNN\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Speaker embedding model used to calculate SIM metric\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"whisper-large-v3\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used to compute WER for non-Chinese languages\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"paraformer-zh\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"ASR model used to compute WER for Chinese language\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VALL-E\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceCraft\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CosyVoice\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"XTTS-v2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"NaturalSpeech 3\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceBox\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HierSpeech++\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LM-VC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UniAudio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC) and Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vevo\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WeSep\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceFilter\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TSELM\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TF-GridNet\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceFixer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SELM\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MaskSR\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Lip2Speech-Unit\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Lip-to-Speech (L2S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"We introduce Metis, a foundation model for unified speech generation. Unlike previous task-specific or multi-task models, Metis follows a pre-training and fine-tuning paradigm. It is pre-trained on large-scale unlabeled speech data using masked generative modeling and then fine-tuned to adapt to diverse speech generation tasks. Specifically, 1) Metis utilizes two discrete speech representations: SSL tokens derived from speech self-supervised learning (SSL) features, and acoustic tokens directly quantized from waveforms. 2) Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens, utilizing 300K hours of diverse speech data, without any additional condition. 3) Through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, Metis achieves efficient adaptation to various speech generation tasks while supporting multimodal input, even when using limited data and trainable parameters. Experiments demonstrate that Metis can serve as a foundation model for unified speech generation: Metis outperforms state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across five speech generation tasks, including zero-shot text-to-speech, voice conversion, target speaker extraction, speech enhancement, and lip-to-speech, even with fewer than 20M trainable parameters or 300 times less training data. Audio samples are are available at https://metis-demo.github.io/.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T04:26:29.908528\"}, \"score\": 2}]\n===TF-LocoFormer===\n[]\n===state space speech===\n[]", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "92329cfa-8e03-4609-b2b7-11a7b4021b4a", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T05:53:36.273Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "[{\"paper\": {\"arxiv_id\": \"2502.03128\", \"title\": \"Metis: A Foundation Speech Generation Model with Masked Generative Pre-training\", \"authors\": [\"Yuancheng Wang\", \"Jiachen Zheng\", \"Junan Zhang\", \"Xueyao Zhang\", \"Huan Liao\", \"Zhizheng Wu\"], \"year\": 2025, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.LG\", \"eess.AS\", \"eess.SP\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u4efb\\u52a1\\u7edf\\u4e00\", \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-\\u53c2\\u8003\\u8bed\\u97f3\"], \"contributions\": [\"Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens using large-scale unlabeled speech data without any task-specific condition.\", \"Metis efficiently adapts to various speech generation tasks through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, achieving state-of-the-art results with limited data and trainable parameters.\", \"Metis supports multimodal conditional inputs during fine-tuning, enabling diverse speech generation tasks and novel applications like text-guided target speaker extraction through multi-task combinations.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2409.00750\", \"title\": \"MaskGCT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS experiments on SeedTTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"w2v-bert-2.0\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"SSL Token extractor using its 17th layer features for the first stage discrete representation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\