le\": \"XTTS-v2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"NaturalSpeech 3\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceBox\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in zero-shot TTS\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HierSpeech++\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LM-VC\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"UniAudio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC) and Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vevo\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Voice Conversion (VC)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WeSep\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceFilter\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TSELM\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Target Speaker Extraction (TSE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"TF-GridNet\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceFixer\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SELM\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MaskSR\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Speech Enhancement (SE)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Lip2Speech-Unit\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Baseline compared against in Lip-to-Speech (L2S)\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"We introduce Metis, a foundation model for unified speech generation. Unlike previous task-specific or multi-task models, Metis follows a pre-training and fine-tuning paradigm. It is pre-trained on large-scale unlabeled speech data using masked generative modeling and then fine-tuned to adapt to diverse speech generation tasks. Specifically, 1) Metis utilizes two discrete speech representations: SSL tokens derived from speech self-supervised learning (SSL) features, and acoustic tokens directly quantized from waveforms. 2) Metis performs masked generative pre-training on SSL tokens, utilizing 300K hours of diverse speech data, without any additional condition. 3) Through fine-tuning with task-specific conditions, Metis achieves efficient adaptation to various speech generation tasks while supporting multimodal input, even when using limited data and trainable parameters. Experiments demonstrate that Metis can serve as a foundation model for unified speech generation: Metis outperforms state-of-the-art task-specific or multi-task systems across five speech generation tasks, including zero-shot text-to-speech, voice conversion, target speaker extraction, speech enhancement, and lip-to-speech, even with fewer than 20M trainable parameters or 300 times less training data. Audio samples are are available at https://metis-demo.github.io/.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-27T04:26:29.908528\"}, \"score\": 2}]\n===TF-LocoFormer===\n[]\n===state space speech===\n[]", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
