{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784872579441", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "关键发现：SPGM (arXiv 2309.12608, ICASSP 2024) 作者与本文作者重叠（Shengkui Zhao, Bin Ma 等），且标题为 \"Prioritizing Local Features for Enhanced Speech Separation\" ——这与本论文的核心观点相同。让我检查一下 SPGM 的细节，并寻找经过验证的 SOTA 排行榜数据。"}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "77d50731-8e54-4798-8417-289c20067f4f"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784872579441", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-8953facb22934917", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.12608\" -o /tmp/spgm.html 2>&1 && python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('/tmp/spgm.html') as f:\n    html = f.read()\n# Extract abstract\nm = re.search(r'<blockquote class=\\\"abstract[^>]*>(.*?)</blockquote>', html, re.DOTALL)\nif m:\n    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', '', m.group(1)).strip()\n    print('SPGM Abstract:', text[:2000])\n\" 2>&1", "description": "Get SPGM abstract"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "2007188c-40fc-4922-9b89-bdd7eea47a39"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784872579441", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-8aa8f77fb457491b", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://sotaverified.org/tasks/speech-separation?dataset=wsj0-2mix\" -o /tmp/sota.html 2>&1 && python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('/tmp/sota.html') as f:\n    html = f.read()\n# Extract table content\ntext = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', html)\ntext = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text)\n# Find the results section\nidx = text.find('Benchmark Results')\nif idx >= 0:\n    print(text[idx:idx+3000])\nelse:\n    print(text[:3000])\n\" 2>&1 | head -60", "description": "Get SOTA leaderboard data"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "bba71dc6-1372-4344-8249-408e77ad2233"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8953facb22934917", "type": "tool_result", "content": "SPGM Abstract: Abstract:Dual-path is a popular architecture for speech separation models (e.g. Sepformer) which splits long sequences into overlapping chunks for its intra- and inter-blocks that separately model intra-chunk local features and inter-chunk global relationships. However, it has been found that inter-blocks, which comprise half a dual-path model&#39;s parameters, contribute minimally to performance. Thus, we propose the Single-Path Global Modulation (SPGM) block to replace inter-blocks. SPGM is named after its structure consisting of a parameter-free global pooling module followed by a modulation module comprising only 2% of the model&#39;s total parameters. The SPGM block allows all transformer layers in the model to be dedicated to local feature modelling, making the overall model single-path. SPGM achieves 22.1 dB SI-SDRi on WSJ0-2Mix and 20.4 dB SI-SDRi on Libri2Mix, exceeding the performance of Sepformer by 0.5 dB and 0.3 dB respectively and matches the performance of recent SOTA models with up to 8 times fewer parameters. Model and weights are available at this http URL", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "9f738fdd-4afe-4d24-b110-e35ffef7b511", "uuid": "f3b1f567-9024-4542-8af9-8177eae175f0", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T05:56:32.238Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "SPGM Abstract: Abstract:Dual-path is a popular architecture for speech separation models (e.g. Sepformer) which splits long sequences into overlapping chunks for its intra- and inter-blocks that separately model intra-chunk local features and inter-chunk global relationships. However, it has been found that inter-blocks, which comprise half a dual-path model&#39;s parameters, contribute minimally to performance. Thus, we propose the Single-Path Global Modulation (SPGM) block to replace inter-blocks. SPGM is named after its structure consisting of a parameter-free global pooling module followed by a modulation module comprising only 2% of the model&#39;s total parameters. The SPGM block allows all transformer layers in the model to be dedicated to local feature modelling, making the overall model single-path. SPGM achieves 22.1 dB SI-SDRi on WSJ0-2Mix and 20.4 dB SI-SDRi on Libri2Mix, exceeding the performance of Sepformer by 0.5 dB and 0.3 dB respectively and matches the performance of recent SOTA models with up to 8 times fewer parameters. Model and weights are available at this http URL", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8aa8f77fb457491b", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Benchmark Results ▼ WSJ0-2mix 40 submissions ↑ higher is better # Model Metric Claimed Verified Status 1 TF-Locoformer (L) + DM SI-SDRi 25.1 — Unverified 2 SepReformer-L SI-SDRi 25.1 — Unverified 3 TF-Locoformer (M) + DM SI-SDRi 24.6 — Unverified 4 TF-Locoformer (L) SI-SDRi 24.2 — Unverified 5 MossFormer2 (L) SI-SDRi 24.1 — Unverified 6 SepTDA (L=12) SI-SDRi 24 — Unverified 7 Separate And Diffuse SI-SDRi 23.9 — Unverified 8 TF-Locoformer (M) SI-SDRi 23.6 — Unverified 9 MossFormer (L) + DM SI-SDRi 22.8 — Unverified 10 TF-Locoformer (S) + DM SI-SDRi 22.8 — Unverified Show all 40 results (self.__next_f=self.__next_f||[]).push([0]) self.__next_f.push([1,\"1:\\\"$Sreact.fragment\\\"\\n3:I[88287,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0bonoyz~rc49q.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0__7pjky1~_cm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0~f9xr51t6yfm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\"],\\\"default\\\"]\\n4:I[74895,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0bonoyz~rc49q.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0__7pjky1~_cm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0~f9xr51t6yfm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\"],\\\"default\\\"]\\n6:I[51858,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0bonoyz~rc49q.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0__7pjky1~_cm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0~f9xr51t6yfm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\"],\\\"OutletBoundary\\\"]\\n7:\\\"$Sreact.suspense\\\"\\na:I[51858,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0bonoyz~rc49q.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0__7pjky1~_cm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0~f9xr51t6yfm.js?dpl=dpl_7tNsjDi6RL87Gr5KNhFEqDdGKqPC\\\"],\\\"ViewportBoundary\\\"]\\nc:I[